HEADWORD: azotemia
<hw>azotemia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>the accumulation
of an abnormally large amount of nitrogen-containing waste products,
such as urea, in the blood; uremia.</def>⟦br⟧
